President Obama has announced his intent to appoint Jerry Patterson and Alice T. Perry as State Representatives for the Gulf Coast Ecosystem Restoration Task Force. The task force was established by an Executive Order to coordinate restoration efforts in the Gulf Coast region and enhance the economic benefits of ecosystem restoration. Jerry Patterson is currently the Texas Land Commissioner and has focused on renewable energy development as well as oil and gas exploration. Alice Perry is the Assistant Director for the Mississippi Department of Environmental Quality and has experience in policy development and environmental conservation.